ila.<br>&nbsp;Kumaran Asan, <br>Vallathol Narayana Menon, <br>Ulloor S Parameswara Iyer, <br>G Sankara Kurup, <br>Changampuzha Krishna Pillai,<br>&nbsp;Chandu Menon, <br>Vaikom Muhammad Basheer.<br>&nbsp;Kesav Dev, <br>Thakazhi Sivasankara Pillai,<br>&nbsp;Ponkunnam Varky,<br>&nbsp;S K Pottakkad<br>&nbsp;and others</span><span class="c9">&nbsp;</span><br class="c4"><ins class="adsbygoogle" data-ad-client="ca-pub-2093713953638788" data-ad-format="link" data-ad-slot="4605198356"></ins><span style="outline: 0px; transition: all 0.3s ease 0s; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(46, 46, 46); font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: large;"><b class="c8">PART – II&nbsp;</b></span><br class="c4"><span class="c11"><b class="c8">STRENGTH OF MATERIALS</b></span><br class="c4"><span class="c1">Simple stress and strain,<br>&nbsp;longitudinal strain,<br>&nbsp;lateral strain, <br>Poison's ratio, <br>Hook's&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">law,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;modulus of&nbsp; rigidity,<br>&nbsp; shear&nbsp; stress,&nbsp; <br>shear&nbsp; strain,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;relationship between elastic&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">constants,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;Friction,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;sliding&nbsp; friction,&nbsp; <br>rolling&nbsp; friction,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;cone&nbsp; of&nbsp; friction,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;centre&nbsp; of&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">gravity,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;moment&nbsp; of&nbsp; inertia,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;shear&nbsp; force&nbsp; and&nbsp; bending moment-<br>&nbsp; types&nbsp; of&nbsp; beams&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">and&nbsp; its&nbsp; loading&nbsp; conditions,&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;shear&nbsp; force&nbsp; and&nbsp; bending&nbsp; moment&nbsp; diagrams&nbsp; <br>and&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">equations in different types of&nbsp; beams <br>and different types of loads -&nbsp; point load,&nbsp;</span><span class="c1">uniform distributed load, cantilever beam,&nbsp; simply supported beam,&nbsp; deflection of&nbsp;</span><span clas